commit.message:
Implement PEP 515: allow underscores in number literals
https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0515/
https://bugs.python.org/issue26331

Practically accepted as of 2016-03-19:
http://thread.gmane.org/gmane.comp.python.devel/156533/focus=156734
extend tests to include an ambiguity in Python 3.x grammar: "e" for exponent or start of "else"
adapt to stricter version of the CPython implementation (that follows the actual PEP)
tighten PEP 515 test to make sure the underscore literals have the correct node type
fix missing attribute error in compiled Cython installation
make test runner exit with non-0 return status on exceptions (this shadowed an actual bug in this branch)

title: Implement PEP 515: allow underscores in number literals
